The paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms and proposes a new algorithm that disentangles the maximum entropy policy into its diverse, constituent policies. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, since the paper focuses on the development of a new reinforcement learning algorithm, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
